headline_main: Things to Do in the Hudson Valley, Oct. 2 to 11, 2015

abstract: For years, the district attorney’s office in Orange County, Calif., has gotten away with unconstitutional abuses.
snippet: For years, the district attorney’s office in Orange County, Calif., has gotten away with unconstitutional abuses.
lead_paragraph: Prosecutors who bend or even break the rules to win a conviction almost never face any punishment. But even given lax controls, the blatant and systemic misconduct in the Orange County district attorney’s office in Southern California stands out. In a scheme that may go back as far as 30 years, prosecutors and the county sheriff’s department have elicited illegal jailhouse confessions, failed to turn over evidence that is favorable to defendants and lied repeatedly in court about what they did.

abstract: The United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit will review a ruling last year that found the state’s capital punishment system to be dysfunctional.
snippet: The United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit will review a ruling last year that found the state’s capital punishment system to be dysfunctional.
lead_paragraph: Whether California’s application of the death penalty is so drawn out and arbitrary that it amounts to cruel and unusual punishment will be argued on Monday before a federal appeals court in Pasadena.

abstract: The justices took on a case against public-sector unions that could deal a severe blow to organized labor.
snippet: The justices took on a case against public-sector unions that could deal a severe blow to organized labor.
lead_paragraph: The Supreme Court on Tuesday agreed to decide whether public-sector unions may require workers who are not members to help pay for collective bargaining. A ruling against them could deal a severe blow to organized labor.

abstract: Governor Jerry Brown wrongly diverted money dedicated to helping troubled borrowers by instead using it to pay down the state’s debt, a judge found.
snippet: Governor Jerry Brown wrongly diverted money dedicated to helping troubled borrowers by instead using it to pay down the state’s debt, a judge found.
lead_paragraph: A court ruled late Friday that California is obligated to return $331 million that it took from a fund designated to help troubled borrowers but instead used to plug holes in the state’s budget.

abstract: Dozens of deaths and more than a thousand injuries were reported in the quake, which came just weeks after the devastating April 25 temblor.

lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — The vegetable markets, streetside dumpling stands and other signs of ordinary life slowly returning to Nepal were violently interrupted Tuesday when another powerful earthquake shook the eastern part of the country less than three weeks after a deadly earthquake left most of it flattened.
